<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{3}{y}=-{36}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{x}+{4}{y}={3}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({9},{3}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --1. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{1}}{{-{{5}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{1}}}{{-{{5}}}}{\left(-{5}{x}+{3}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{1}}}{{-{{5}}}}{\left(-{36}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{1}\right)}{x}+-{0.6}{y}={7.2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{x}+{4}{y}={3}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3.4}{y}={10.2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{10.2}}{{3.4}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={3}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{3}{\left({3}\right)}=-{36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{\left({9}\right)}=-{36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}=-{36}-{\left({9}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}=-{45}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{45}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={9}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({9},{3}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>